  "prompt": "Is it difficult to get in Munich University?",
  "response": "Getting into the Ludwig Maximilian University of Munich (LMU Munich) can be competitive, depending on the specific program and your qualifications. Some key points:\n\n1. Admission Requirements:\n- High academic performance\n- Good German language skills (for most programs)\n- Specific entrance qualifications for different faculties\n- Some programs have limited enrollment (numerus clausus)\n\n2. Difficulty Levels:\n- Competitive programs like medicine, psychology, and business are harder to get into\n- STEM fields and popular humanities courses can be challenging\n- Some programs have strict selection criteria and entrance exams\n\n3. International Students:\n- Additional requirements like language proficiency tests\n- May need to complete a preparatory course\n- Competitive for international student spots\n\n4. Average Acceptance Rates:\n- Varies by program, but generally around 20-40% acceptance rate\n- More selective programs might have lower acceptance rates\n\nOverall, admission is achievable with strong academic credentials, good language skills, and preparation, but it requires effort and meeting specific criteria.\n\nFor precise, up-to-date information, I recommend checking the university's official website or contacting their admissions office directly.",
